& [SourceSet] is the bounded source-transfer frame
  + [source_001] is Bertolini, Darmon, and Prasanna, Chow-Heegner points on CM elliptic curves and values of p-adic L-functions
    = link: https://www.math.mcgill.ca/darmon/pub/Articles/Research/53.BDP3/paper.pdf
    = use: outlines a construction of rational points on CM elliptic curves using cycles on higher-dimensional varieties, with p-adic rationality results
  + [source_002] is Bertolini, Darmon, and Prasanna, Generalized Heegner cycles and p-adic Rankin L-series
    = link: https://sites.lsa.umich.edu/kartikp/wp-content/uploads/sites/1326/2024/07/BDP1.pdf
    = use: relates generalized Heegner cycles under p-adic Abel-Jacobi maps to special values of p-adic Rankin L-series
  + [source_003] is Darmon, Daub, Lichtenstein, and Rotger, Algorithms for Chow-Heegner points via iterated integrals
    = link: https://wstein.org/papers/mcom2927-chow-heegner.pdf
    = use: gives algorithms for computing Chow-Heegner points and reports rank-one computations in small conductor examples
  + [source_004] is Darmon, Rotger, and Sols, Iterated integrals, diagonal cycles and rational points on elliptic curves
    = link: https://www.numdam.org/articles/10.5802/pmb.a-145/
    = use: connects diagonal cycles and iterated integrals to rational points on elliptic curves in special settings
  + [source_005] is Castella, Heegner cycles and p-adic L-functions
    = link: https://web.math.ucsb.edu/~castella/HeegnerCycles-print.pdf
    = use: shows Heegner-cycle and p-adic L-function machinery can yield rank-zero Bloch-Kato type consequences in certain higher-weight settings

& [ResearchFindings] is the source-transfer result
  + [finding_001] is Chow-Heegner points are a genuine source-transfer mechanism in special settings
    = meaning: the R-hand "growth" phrase has a sharper formal neighbor than generic diagonal cycles alone
  + [finding_002] is the transfer can land in rational points on elliptic curves
    = meaning: source transfer is not wholly blocked; the boundary is scope and sufficiency, not impossibility
  + [finding_003] is the known transfer is special-family and hypothesis dependent
    = meaning: CM, modular, correspondence, p-adic, Tate-conjectural, or rank-one style conditions remain part of the statement
  + [finding_004] is computations and constructions do not become an all-rank source-count theorem
    = meaning: producing some Chow-Heegner points is not the same as producing enough independent generators for arbitrary analytic rank
  + [finding_005] is independence and upper-control compatibility remain separate locks
    = meaning: even successful point construction must still be paired with height/regulator independence and Selmer upper bounds

& [BoundaryUpdate] is the adjusted BSD state
  + [old_boundary] is no source transfer from special higher-cycle objects into enough independent Mordell-Weil points
  + [adjusted_boundary] is source transfer exists in special Chow-Heegner and related settings, but no general sufficiency theorem supplies enough independent Mordell-Weil generators for arbitrary BSD rank
  + [best_new_shape] is BSD source transfer should be studied through Chow-Heegner point corridors rather than generic diagonal cycles
  + [first_remaining_lock] is sufficiency of source count and independence for arbitrary analytic rank
  + [second_remaining_lock] is compatible upper-control system in the same hypotheses
  + [proof_promotion] is blocked
    = reason: special point construction does not close rank equality or leading coefficient formula for general BSD

& [NextInquiry] is the next local target
  + [recommended_next] is build a BSD Source Transfer Sufficiency Ledger if the next heartbeat continues BSD
